        <abstract>
            <t>DDoS attacks take place every day globally.  Like Virus Definitions,
   data sharing among DDoS mitigation service providers becomes
   important because it can avoid repeating same detection and
   classification work when the providers try to denfense DDoS attacks.</t>
   <t>This document describes possible mechanisms which implement the data
   sharing cooperative DDoS protection.  The described data models are
   compatible with DOTS protocol.</t>
        </abstract>
